result.execSummary:
The defendant Jordan J English was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).
  • Sex with Child Age 16 or Older, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.09.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

case called at 9:16am.
Defendant Jordan J English in court with Attorney Joseph F. Fischer. ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Clerk of Courts Cindy Hamre-Incha in court.

This hearing was scheduled by the Court in regard to the issue of  how the Clerk would be able to process the file if Mr. English becomes eligible for expungement on Count #2, in as much as it is the Information contains two counts and there were convictions on two counts; the Court only made Mr. English eligible for expungement as to Count #2, with the intent being that Count #1 will be dismissed outright. 

The Court summarizes an off-record discussion that resulted in the plan that if Mr. English successfully completes his Probation term , he is to notify the Court using the State-form Petition; at that point the State will file an Amended Information under the case #10CF1-B that relates to Count #1; the Clerk will create a new file upon receipt of that Amended Information and that #10CF1-B file will be expunged.
